The paper deals with the construction of a spanning tree with constant average distortion, which is a problem in graph theory and optimization (cs.DS). The paper also makes use of notions of distortion for metric embedding, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The construction of the spanning tree involves techniques from computational geometry, which is a subfield of computer science (cs.CG). The paper also involves optimization techniques, which is a topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper discusses the use of prioritized distortion, which is a property relevant to machine learning and data analysis (cs.SI).
